---
title: One-Pan Tex-Mex Organic Beef Tacos with Pineapple, Pickled Veggies & Lime Crema
description: We’re obsessed with sweet and savory flavor combos for dinner, which is why we have a soft spot for tacos al pastor. The dish traditionally involves pork marinated in pineapple juice and spices, then slowly spit-roasted for ultra-tender results. In this riff on the classic, we skip the slow-cooking by swapping out the pork shoulder for ground pork. It’s browned with a bounty of Southwest spices, simmered with chunks of pineapple until saucy, and stuffed into warm tortillas with lime crema and pickled onion and radish. You can have all that in just 30 minutes—taco ’bout a dinner winner!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/638fa8be3a741a117102c28e-a7aca882.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64f8db57d6d437ce24b89ce2.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-tex-mex-organic-beef-tacos-64f8db57d6d437ce24b89ce2
course: main course
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1600 mg
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and
thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine radishes, juice from half the lime,
¼ of the onion, and a big pinch of @salt{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave
until veggies are slightly pink, ~{30-45%seconds}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} with lime zest. Add
water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
pineapple and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until browned
and caramelized, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @organic ground beef{10%oz} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}. Cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, caramelized pineapple, and reserved pineapple juice
until mixture is saucy and combined.

> Swap in beef or organic beef for pork. Cook through remainder of step as instructed.

While pork cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave
until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with pork mixture, lime crema, and as
many pickled veggies (draining first) as you like. Pick @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves
from stems; tear leaves into pieces and sprinkle over tacos. Serve with any
remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.